<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-wyrd-default">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <!-- Hero Image -->
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3 class="lora-semibold">Branches of Magic</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="position-relative p-0">
                    <img class="img-fluid w-100 object-fit-cover" src="/img/banners/magic.png" />
                    <div class="position-absolute bottom-0 end-0 p-3 w-50">
                        <div class="bg-black p-3 bg-opacity-75 rounded shadow">
                            <span class="lora-medium fst-italic text-light">
                                There is no harmless spell. Only consequences too distant to recognize.
                            </span>
                            <span></span>
                            <div class="lora-semibold text-light text-end mt-2">
                                Master Varro, Foundations of Practical Magic
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>
                            Magic is a quiet but undeniable part of the world, woven into its history, faiths,
                            and ceremonies. It exists alongside the natural order rather than replacing it, revealing
                            itself in subtle blessings, ancient curses, and forgotten relics.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Although magic is real, it remains uncommon enough to inspire respect. A village healer,
                            hedge witch, or temple cleric may be the only practitioner many people ever know personally.
                            Powerful spellcasters are rare, and tales of ancient relics, forgotten ruins, and
                            supernatural creatures belong more often to wandering adventurers than to ordinary folk.
                            Nonetheless, every generation produces a handful of individuals capable of far greater
                            feats.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Magic takes many forms, and no single theory fully explains its workings. Scholars study
                            ancient principles to shape arcane forces, priests invoke miracles through devotion, shamans
                            bargain with spirits, witches preserve forgotten rites, and occultists pursue dangerous
                            secrets hidden beneath accepted knowledge. Their methods differ, but all draw upon the same
                            deeper reality that lies beyond the mortal realms.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Traditions of magic can generally be classified by the source of their power and the means
                            by which that power is directed.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">Arcane Magic</h6>
                        <p>
                            Arcane magic is the art of shaping the world through study, formula, and deliberate craft.
                            Its practitioners learn their spells through scrolls, instruction, and long hours of
                            analysis, treating magic as a discipline that rewards precision and patience.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">Sacred Magic</h6>
                        <p>
                            Sacred magic is derived from faith, devotion, and the cultivation of a connection to powers
                            beyond the material world. Its practitioners draw on conviction, intuition, and connection
                            to forces older than language to bend the world to their intent.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>